<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='738772' id='t-738772'>You can see physically,
people become more stressed.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='741396' id='t-741396'>What he finds is that the couples
who manage that feeling of stress</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='747178' id='t-747178'>with laughter,
positive emotions like laughter,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='750684' id='t-750684'>not only immediately become less stressed,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='754492' id='t-754492'>they can see them
physically feeling better,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='756906' id='t-756906'>they're dealing with this
unpleasant situation better together,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='760064' id='t-760064'>they are also the couples that report</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='761885' id='t-761885'>high levels of satisfaction
in their relationship</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='764244' id='t-764244'>and they stay together for longer.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='765915' id='t-765915'>So in fact, when you look
at close relationships,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='768236' id='t-768236'>laughter is a phenomenally useful index</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='770134' id='t-770134'>of how people are regulating
